OL,3,CAncient tree which inspired Brambly
OL,4,CHedge cottage discovered in Epping
OL,5,CForest
OL,7,FAn over 300-year-old tree which
OL,8,Finspired the cottage in the Brambly
OL,9,FHedge books, has been discovered in
OL,10,FEpping Forest.
OL,12,FIt is a distinctive crab apple tree,
OL,13,Fwhich was at the heart of Jill
OL,14,FBarklem's illustration of Crabapple
OL,15,FCottage in the beloved children's
OL,16,Fseries.
OL,18,FThe tree is believed to be the only
OL,19,Fknown pollarded tree of its species in
OL,20,Fthe forest, standing near Barn Hoppitt
OL,21,Fand Warren Pond.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/7
